<p><b>Follow-up to decision 1/107:  Incitement to racial and religious hatred and the promotion 
of tolerance 
</b></p>
<p>142. At the 8th meeting, on 21 September 2006, pursuant to Council decision 1/107 
of 30 June 2006, Ms. Mehr Khan Williams, the United Nations Deputy High Commissioner for 
Human Rights, presented the report of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights 
(A/HRC/2/6), and Ms. Asma Jahangir, Special Rapporteur on freedom of religion or belief, and 
Mr. Doudou Di&#232;ne, Special Rapporteur on contemporary forms of racism, racial discrimination, 
xenophobia and related intolerance, presented their joint report (A/HRC/2/3). 
</p><p>143. During the ensuing interactive dialogue, at the 8th meeting, on 21 September 2006, and at 
the 9th meeting, on 22 September 2006, the following made statements and put questions to 
Mr. Di&#232;ne, Ms. Jahangir and Ms. Williams: </p>

 <p> 
</p>
